headline: S&P 500 Gains and Losses Today: NXP Semiconductors Stock Falls as CEO Plans Departure
summary: The S&P 500 advanced 0.6% on Tuesday, April 29, notching a sixth straight winning session. The White House signaled it would soften some tariffs on the auto industry.

headline: SBA Communications (NasdaqGS:SBAC) Reports Increased Net Income & $1,500M Buyback Program
summary: SBA Communications (NasdaqGS:SBAC) recently experienced a notable 10.7% price increase over the last quarter, a movement potentially aided by the company's robust Q1 earnings report released on April 28, 2025. Despite a slight decline in sales, SBA saw its net income rise to $191.8 million from $154.5 million, and its diluted EPS improved to $1.77 from $1.42. Furthermore, the announcement of a significant $1,500 million share buyback program and a steady quarterly dividend of $1.11 per share...

headline: SBA Communications Corporation to Speak at The JP Morgan 53rd Annual Global Technology, Media and Communications Conference
summary: BOCA RATON, Fla., April 29, 2025--SBA Communications Corporation (NASDAQ: SBAC) ("SBA") announces that Marc Montagner, Chief Financial Officer is scheduled to speak at the JP Morgan 53rd Annual Global Technology, Media and Communications Conference, Tuesday, May 13, 2025 at 5:10pm ET. The conference will be at The Westin Boston Seaport District in Boston, Massachusetts. The audio presentation for SBA can be accessed by visiting www.sbasite.com.
